It’s my job to tell stories and report the news but like everyone, I’m struggling to find the right words. Nothing seems adequate or sufficient. 
After work yesterday I went home and hugged Andi, like I always do. I cried. And she just smiled and said hi mommy! We spent the afternoon playing in the sunshine and cuddling on the couch. A beautiful day I can’t help but feel guilty for. 
Evelyn, Hallie, William, Cynthia, Katherine and Mike.

repost via @wkrntv 
I was just having a conversation with someone the other day about how I read horrible stories every day on air and still keep it together… I’ve somehow always been able to compartmentalize stories, “In one ear, and out the other,” I would always say… I often joke that I never know what the weather is because I just don’t listen… so I can sleep at night.

Today was different and I can’t compartmentalize this anymore. I I broke on Monday when I was first out in Green Hills, but I think I’ve just been running on adrenaline and auto-pilot since then. 

Then this morning as more details came out, I just hit a wall and I broke.

I almost didn’t share this video because it’s not about me and any sympathy should be directed towards these sweet innocent families. But my friends encouraged me and said it might help other people know that it’s OK to not be OK. Thankful my friend Neil was able to carry on for me.

Praying for strength and healing for all. ❤️

I cannot believe I’m posting video of this. Not that I have Tourette’s, but me actually ‘ticking.’ @megtomwx is so open about her disability and is always encouraging me to talk more about mine. I’m not embarrassed that I have TS, but I’ve spent my entire life hiding my tics. Doing them when I think no one is looking or “dumbing them down.” To do them on camera is terrifying. But today is #disabilityindependenceday - and I couldn’t think of a better day for us to share openly about our disabilities - and how they’ve only made us stronger.

What a special day yesterday meeting this incredible person. @baylen_dupree and I connected on social media and finally got to hang out. We talked about our tics, growing up with TS and what it’s like living with it. This girl is SO brave and is using her voice and platform to help so many people with tics… including me. The #NICU is not a club any parent chooses to be in - but if we could choose it would be this community. Yesterday was Andi’s first official #nicu graduation party since the pandemic. We got to see so many of her nurses & doctors who helped save her life and take care of her until she was ready to come home.

We talked to one of her amazing doctors - and I vividly remember when Andi was very sick with a blood infection, and said we should go to the chapel to pray. We did. And 71 days later she came home. We are forever grateful to you all for our tiny little miracle.

Yes, it is. But I wouldn’t want any other schedule. While I do go to bed early and miss out on a lot of fun events,I don’t miss the important stuff. Every day after the show I run home to give andi a kiss before she goes to school. And then I can pick her up after school and go on adventures or dance class or just to get ice cream. We have the whole afternoon together… I know this time is so precious.

It’s important to me that she sees me working every day and doing something I love, but that she also knows she my priority, and the sacrifices (sleep) are well worth it.

Thank you to everyone who came out to shop & raise money for @proverbs1210animalrescue! And thank you to @veronicabeard & @carolinegmazey for hosting us and giving back to such a deserving non-profit. Proverbs is a foster-based rescue, meaning they rely on volunteers & foster families to help save animals… that, and donations. 

They help those that do not have a voice - like these animals - and especially sweet Bennett, whose story you may have seen. He was locked in a cage and left to starve to death. Thanks to Proverbs, he’s recovering in a foster home and getting stronger and healthier every day. 

Your donations help save lives. And PS - Blake, Toodles and the sister kitties are all up for adoption! If you are looking for a new family member this holiday season, please consider adoption. And if you missed the fundraiser - it’s not too late! 🫶
